---

# 2. Parabolic Move Exit

If ETF moves vertically too fast:

| Condition                       | Action                   |
| ------------------------------- | ------------------------ |
| ETF up >15% in <20 trading days | Book partial/full profit |
| RSI > 80 weekly                 | Tighten exit             |
| Massive retail euphoria         | Reduce aggressively      |

Especially important for:

* Silver,
* Nasdaq AI rallies.

---

# 3. Trend Breakdown Exit

Professionals often use:

## 50 DMA / 200 DMA logic

Example:

| Condition                | Action            |
| ------------------------ | ----------------- |
| Close below 50 DMA       | Stop fresh buying |
| Close below 200 DMA      | Reduce exposure   |
| Lower highs + lower lows | Tighten targets   |

This avoids holding through secular breakdowns.

---

# 4. Time-Based Exit (Very Important)

Sometimes:
ETF stays dead money for months.

So use:

| Rule                          | Action         |
| ----------------------------- | -------------- |
| No recovery after 9–12 months | Exit partial   |
| Opportunity cost high         | Rotate capital |

Professionals always consider:

> opportunity cost.

---

# 5. Macro Sell Trigger

Especially relevant for your portfolio.

## Nasdaq

Sell/reduce when:

* Fed tightening aggressively,
* yields exploding higher,
* AI capex cycle slowing.

## Gold/Silver

Sell/reduce when:

* real yields rising strongly,
* DXY surging,
* inflation collapsing.

